================================================================================
                    WHAT ARE COMPONENTS IN REACT?
================================================================================

A component is a reusable, independent piece of UI (User Interface) in React.
It's the basic building block of any React application.

KEY CHARACTERISTICS:
- Reusable: Can be used multiple times throughout your application
- Independent: Has its own logic, styles, and state
- Composable: Components can contain other components
- Modular: Easy to maintain and update

================================================================================
                    TWO TYPES OF COMPONENTS
================================================================================

1. FUNCTIONAL COMPONENTS
   - JavaScript functions that return JSX
   - Modern approach (hooks available)
   - Simpler and preferred in modern React

2. CLASS COMPONENTS
   - JavaScript classes extending React.Component
   - Older approach
   - Have lifecycle methods


================================================================================
                    EXAMPLE 1: FUNCTIONAL COMPONENT (Button)
================================================================================

function Button() {
  return (
    <button style={{
      padding: '10px 20px',
      backgroundColor: '#007bff',
      color: 'white',
      border: 'none',
      borderRadius: '5px',
      cursor: 'pointer'
    }}>
      Click Me!
    </button>
  );
}

export default Button;

// Usage:
// <Button />


